AU  - Asdrubali, Pierfederico
AU  - Sørensen, Bent E.
AU  - Yosha, Oved
T1  - Channels of Interstate Risk Sharing: United States 1963–1990*
PY  - 1996
Y1  - 1996/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/2946708
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 111
IS  - 4
SP  - 1081
EP  - 1110
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We develop a framework for quantifying the amount of risk sharing among states in the United States, and construct data that allow us to decompose the cross-sectional variance in gross state product into several components which we refer to as levels of smoothing. We find that 39 percent of shocks to gross state product are smoothed by capital markets, 13 percent are smoothed by the federal government, and 23 percent are smoothed by credit markets. The remaining 25 percent are not smoothed. We also decompose the federal government smoothing into subcategories: taxes, transfers, and grants to states.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2946708
ER  - 



