T1  - Tax Subsidies and Household Saving: Evidence from Canada*
PY  - 1996
Y1  - 1996/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/2946714
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 111
IS  - 4
SP  - 1237
EP  - 1268
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Targeted tax-based saving incentives can be a powerful tool for promoting household and national saving. This study examines the effect of the cancellation of the Registered Home Ownership Savings Plan (RHOSP), a Canadian tax-subsidized saving program, on household saving. The cancellation provides exogenous variation in eligibility for the subsidy that is uncorrelated with householdspecific heterogeneity in saving behavior. The empirical analysis suggests that the subsidy had a substantial impact on saving: each dollar contributed to the program represented 56-93 and 20-57 cents of new household and national saving, respectively.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2946714
